        Personally I think the charts should mostly be about new music. Of course, there are valid reasons for songs to chart again but with all the great music out there being made today it seems such a shame that ancient hits, however good they are, take the place of current music.         WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (02/10/2020 - 09/10/2020)

        🔴 (Negative)

        1) ‘Take You Dancing’ just won’t leave! The more I hear the hook on the radio, the more I get creeped out by it. At least it finally fell!

        2) ‘Head & Heart’ is out of the Top 10! I’m happy that this song got six weeks at the top, but it doesn’t deserve to fall this fast. I feel so warm inside every time I hear it!

        3) ‘Lighter’ completely crashed following being struck by ACR! I’d have loved to see this go all the way, but now I can only hope that it stabilises & gets a decent placing in the yearly chart!

        4) As if ACR didn’t p!$$ me off enough already, it also took out both ‘Cardigan’ & ‘Exile’ almost entirely! I’m so sad that Taylor Swift dropped back a lot this week, but at least ‘Folklore’ itself is sticking around on the albums chart & both of these hits got widespread critical acclaim.

        5) Oh yeah, sadly, ‘Daisy’ is here! Not only does Ashnikko sound incredibly offbeat, but her “singing” becomes more screeching on the hook. Ultimately, it’s just too annoying to revisit & without Radio 1’s overplayment of this, I don’t see how it would've made it here! I’d skip it.

        6) Sadly, it looks like ‘Rain On Me’ is leaving next week! Oh well, I’m just happy that Lady Gaga is still getting hits over 10 years after her most successful era.

        7) 'Hallucinate' is out of the Top 40, meaning Dua Lipa doesn't have any songs in the region now!

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) ‘Tick Tock’ didn’t make the Top 10 this week, but it’s here because I think it’ll enter next week! I really like all three artists here, so this was always bound to work, especially when I’ve been anticipating a Clean Bandit comeback for so long.

        2) ‘What You Know Bout Love’ is really starting to become massive everywhere now! I don’t have the same connection to Pop Smoke’s music that most other regulars here do, but I have heard the album & I can definitely see why this is the next single.

        3) I only know Dutchavelli ironically from ‘I Dunno’, but man, he sounds fired up here! The production is menacing enough to give him some real punch, although I’m not sure on the mix at points. Overall though, I think this certainly has potential to become bigger, which I actually wouldn’t mind! ‘808’ might’ve been the bigger debut today, but this one is going to stand out for me personally.

        4) I’m really not sure how I feel about ‘Franchise’ right now! On one hand, the beat hits really hard & Travis Scott actually sounds in full control of his own song for the first time since probably ‘Sicko Mode’, but Young Thug’s vocals are so grating here & MIA’s vocals are pushed so far back. It honestly completely ruins what could’ve been a mostly enjoyable trap hit!

        5) ‘Miss Me’ seems to have a more chilled vibe from MoStack & AJ Tracey than I would’ve expected! I prefer them as MC where they’re dropping hard-hitting bangers, but this has a somewhat summery vibe to it & at least the two of them have decent chemistry, so yeah, I’ll take it.

        6) That new Everton song might’ve been nowhere close to the Top 40 overall, but it was the best-selling song of the week. Being a Liverpool supporter, I think you all know my thoughts on that already! At least we’re above them in the Premier League table now, haha.

        🟢 (Positive)

        1) ‘Mood’ stays at #1 with an even bigger lead than last week! Honestly, I wouldn’t even mind if this gets another month at the top. It’s definitely the catchiest trap song of 2020 so far!

        2) ‘Lemonade’s continued ascent on Spotify puts it in the Top 5 overall! I genuinely never expected it to be in this section, but that just reflects how much it grew on me, especially that hook, haha.

        3) ‘Midnight Sky’ is back! It’s the most listened to song on the radio right now & I’m so glad that the British public are keeping it this high up too. Those vocals are just incredible!

        4) ‘You Broke Me First’ is also finally in the Top 10! I totally agree with the Billie Eilish comparisons, which I mean as a massive compliment. I really hope Tate McRae can get more hits if they sound anything like this!

        5) ‘Lasting Lover’ might not have gained in streaming, but it does significantly in both sales & airplay! I never would’ve expected James Arthur to be the right fit for an EDM banger, but his raw vocals really suit Sigala’s bouncy production here.

        6) Okay, I was excited to see that ‘My Ex’s Best Friend’ was making the chart on Monday’s update, but then I just heard ‘Forget Me Too’ on the chart show & man, I’m so happy that MGK transitioned from rap to punk! This sound definitely suits his more aggressive delivery & Halsey sounds incredible alongside him on the latter; certainly more than Blackbear’s verse on the former. Overall though, these two songs have actually convinced me to check out the entirety of his new album, they’re that impressive!

        7) IDLES score a massive #1 debut on the albums chart, outselling the rest of the Top 5 combined! Their numbers were impressive, but I can’t really speak on their music itself, as I haven’t heard enough of their songs to comment there. Why are they in the positive section then? Because a Bristol act have the #1 album of the week! That’s where I’m currently living, haha.

        Thanks for reading everyone! Have a nice weekend. :)
